            "id": "devotion",
            "type": "devotion",
            "title": "Daily Devotional",
            "value": "%3Cp%3EThe%20twenty-six%20letters%20of%20the%20Hebrew%20alphabet%20are%20used%20to%20begin%20the%20twenty-six%20verses%20of%20Psalm%20136.%20Twenty-six%20times%20the%20Holy%20Spirit%20wants%20us%20to%20know%20that%20%22His%20faithful%20loves%20endures%20forever.%22%20This%20fact%20should%20be%20branded%20upon%20our%20minds%20and%20hearts%20both%20now%20and%20always.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EIn%20stark%20contrast%20to%20this%20message%20is%20the%20incredible%20judgment%20of%20the%20seventh%20seal%20(Revelation%208).%20Death%2C%20darkness%2C%20and%20despair%20consume%20the%20earth%20with%20fiery%20hail%2C%20falling%20stars%2C%20and%20bitter%20waters.%20How%20does%20this%20judgment%20show%20a%20God%20whose%20love%20endures%20forever%3F%20Nahum%20provides%20the%20answer%3A%20%22The%20Lord%20is%20slow%20to%20get%20angry%2C%20but%20his%20power%20is%20great%2C%20and%20he%20never%20lets%20the%20guilty%20go%20unpunished.%20He%20displays%20his%20power%20in%20the%20whirlwind%20and%20the%20storm.%20The%20billowing%20clouds%20are%20the%20dust%20beneath%20his%20feet%22%20(Nahum%201%3A3).%20God%20shows%20His%20love%20by%20waiting%20so%20long%20to%20impose%20judgment!%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3ECenturies%20have%20gone%20by%20with%20God's%20long-suffering%2C%20restraining%20judgment%20being%20withheld%2C%20just%20as%20He%20withheld%20in%20the%20days%20of%20Noah.%20God%20also%20waited%20patiently%20for%20Pharaoh%2C%20though%20He%20%22killed%20the%20firstborn%20of%20Egypt%22%20(Psalm%20136%3A10).%20The%20old%20idea%20that%20a%20God%20of%20love%20cannot%20show%20wrath%20is%20wrong.%20His%20love%20is%20shown%20by%20the%20fact%20that%20He%20waits%20so%20long%20to%20display%20His%20wrath!%20%3C%2Fp%3E%0A"
        },
